Fresh-eyes review complete for `src/blog/people/drafts/Madelaine-Petsch.md`. The notes are appended as a `FRESH EYES REVIEW (2026-07-09)` comment block at the bottom of the file — no body edits were made.

The two biggest issues flagged:

1. **Cheryl Blossom is frozen at season one.** The draft only frames her as a "menace"/"bully," but the character's defining public arc — coming out as bisexual, the Choni relationship, and Petsch fighting the writers' room for that representation while fans told her the character helped them accept themselves — is completely missing. It's both the most obvious reader-expectation gap and a missed thesis-reinforcer: she spent seven seasons fixing her own character.
2. **The mother thread never closes.** The outbound-only phone rule covers *both* parents and the resentment lands on "everyone in my family," but the ending litigates only dad — mom stays a plot device.

Also worth knowing: the current-tense anchor is stale — *The Strangers: Chapter 3* released February 6, 2026 and Petsch has said she's walking away from the franchise "for my own mental health," which is arc-relevant material (the fixer learning to quit). Smaller notes cover trims (the age-8 night is touched five times, the Cartier rings three) and a TL;DR bullet that pre-spends the ending's payoff. The review also flags what to preserve: the "Four Phone Calls" section, the YouTube empathy turn, and the ending.

Sources: [Nylon — Petsch on Choni shippers](https://www.nylon.com/articles/madelaine-petsch-riverdale-choni-interview), [Capital — Petsch confirms Cheryl is bisexual](https://www.capitalfm.com/news/tv-film/is-cheryl-blossom-bisexual/), [Refinery29 — Cheryl's coming out](https://www.refinery29.com/en-us/2018/03/192895/cheryl-coming-out-bisexual-riverdale-season-2), [THR — Chapter 3 ending interview](https://www.hollywoodreporter.com/movies/movie-features/the-strangers-chapter-3-star-madelaine-petsch-1236496498/), [Wikipedia — The Strangers: Chapter 3](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/The_Strangers_%E2%80%93_Chapter_3)
